                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.51/190: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-05-02T15:00:00-04:32">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1923—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Bankers’ representatives today presented to the President a proposition that
                    he grant provisional power of attorney without prejudice to Bolivia’s position
                    in the proposed discussions in New York with the President’s committee. He
                    appeared favorably disposed and it is probable that power of attorney will be
                    adjusted. Committee expects to leave for the United States next week. The
                    Bolivian Government has remitted June service of the loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cottrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
